Philippines Offers to Buy Back $1.5 Billion of Dollar Debt

-- B y   K a r l   L e s t e r   M .   Y a p
-- 
2011-10-10T06:14:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/philippines-offers-to-buy-back-1-5-billion-of-dollar-debt.html
The  Philippines  has started
accepting offers for a buyback of $1.5 billion of dollar-
denominated bonds, Finance Undersecretary Rosalia de Leon said
in  Manila  today.  Around $17 billion of debt is eligible for the buyback and
the government will announce the result of the offer on Oct. 14,
de Leon said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karl Lester M. Yap in Manila at 
 kyap5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shamim Adam at 
 sadam2@bloomberg.net  